1. Shifty Shellshock is best known as a co-founder and front man of the rap rock band Crazy Town, and his vocal style includes both growling and clean vocals. However, Crazy Town is categorized as a rap rock band, not specifically death metal.

2. Alissa White-Gluz is a Canadian vocalist best known as the lead vocalist of the Swedish melodic death metal band Arch Enemy. She has also been a member of the Canadian metalcore band the Agonist, which does incorporate elements of death metal.

3. While both vocalists use growled and clean vocals, Shifty Shellshock is primarily associated with rap rock, whereas Alissa White-Gluz is primarily associated with melodic death metal and metalcore. Therefore, it is not accurate to categorize both of them exclusively as death metal vocalists, although Alissa White-Gluz is more closely associated with death metal than Shifty Shellshock.
